# Auto commit + push (laravel13.x)

When you **finish substantive implementation** (features, docs deliverables, fixes the user requested), **commit and push without asking** — unless the user said question-only, review-only, or explicitly said not to commit/push this session.

## Do automatically after completed work

1. Run in **parallel**: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -5 --oneline`
2. Draft a Conventional Commits message (why > what); subject concise; body when needed
3. **Do not** stage `.env`, credentials, or `tools/tiktok-metadata/downloads/`
4. Commit via HEREDOC:

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
subject line

Optional body.
EOF
)"
```

5. `git pull --rebase origin main` (or current branch) if push may be non-fast-forward
6. `git push -u origin HEAD` (or `git push origin <branch>`)
7. Report commit hash + branch in the completion summary

## Git safety (always)

- NEVER update git config; NEVER force-push main/master; NEVER skip hooks unless user asked
- NEVER commit secrets; warn if user explicitly asked to commit sensitive files
- NEVER amend unless user rules allow (hook auto-fix on your commit, unpushed, etc.)
- If commit hook fails: fix and **new** commit — do not amend a failed commit

## When NOT to auto commit/push

- User only asked a question or review (no code/docs change)
- No changes to commit
- User said "don't commit" / "don't push" in this thread
- Work is intentionally WIP and user asked to stop mid-task

## Commit message style

Match recent repo history (often short `type: description` subjects). Prefer `docs:`, `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:` as appropriate.
